[5] USA (New York): new cases spreading
Date: Thu 30 May 2019
Source: Silive [abridged, edited]
https://www.silive.com/news/2019/05/5-things-to-know-about-measles-following-announcement-of-7-borough-cases.html


The city Department of Health and Mental Hygiene (DOHMH) announced on Wed [29 May 2019] that 7 measles cases have been reported in Staten Island since the beginning of the outbreak in October 2019. Six of those cases occurred in March 2019 but were only recently reported to DOHMH.

Now that Staten Island has officially become part of the disease's resurgence in the United States, here are some facts to know:
The MMR vaccine works, and medical professionals say it's safe. Despite what anonymous ramblings on the internet might suggest, medical professionals say that the measles, mumps and rubella (MMR) vaccine is safe. "When the proper schedule is followed, measles immunity is usually lifelong," he said. "It's a very good vaccine."

[byline: Paul Liotta]

