[7] California (Santa Barbara)
Date: Fri 31 May 2019
Source: Edhat from Santa Barbara County Public Health Department [abridged, edited]
https://www.edhat.com/news/first-measles-case-of-2019-reaches-santa-barbara


The Santa Barbara County Public Health Department (PHD) has confirmed the 1st case of measles in the county since 2016. The person identified is a resident of Santa Barbara in his 20s. The individual is considered infectious between 25 May 2019 through 2 Jun 2019 but has been in isolation since 29 May 2019.

The PHD is confident that the exposure was limited, as the individual spent much of his infectious period outside the county of Santa Barbara. At this time, the PHD is involved in contacting and interviewing persons who may have been exposed to the individual to confirm immunization and immunity status. PHD is also working closely with Riverside County, Los Angeles County, Ventura County, and San Francisco, as the individual traveled to these areas during his infectious period.

