[10] New Zealand (MidCentral District)
Date: Fri 31 May 2019
Source: Stuff [abridged, edited]
https://www.stuff.co.nz/manawatu-standard/news/113161785/measles-case-confirmed-in-region-covered-by-midcentral-district-health-board


A case of measles has been confirmed in the region covered by the MidCentral District Health Board this week. Medical officer of health Rob Weir confirmed the case and said MidCentral's public health service had acted to minimise the risk of further spread.

When asked where in the region the case was, a MidCentral spokeswoman said the patient lived in the southern part but had travelled to other parts while potentially infectious. "The patient has been in quarantine following contact with a confirmed case out of the region," Weir said. "However, there is a period of time before entering quarantine when the patient was infectious."

