[11] Indonesia
Date: Sat 1 Jun 2019
Source: ABC [abridged, edited]
https://www.abc.net.au/radio/programs/am/measles-on-the-rise-in-indonesia,-fears-of-impact-on-australia/11168380


Health authorities fear an increase in measles cases in Australia could worsen unless vaccination rates in South East Asia improve. Indonesia poses the biggest risk, with a UN report showing that 1.2 million children across the country have missed out on the measles jab.

[byline: Anne Barker]

